<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-24T20:23:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-24T20:23:00-05:00" n="1077" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1077">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3793.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-24T18:00:00-07:23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At 8 o’clock last night committee Mexicans notified Americans in Nacozari
                            they must leave. Train was assembled, Americans were disarmed and placed
                            aboard. All arrived safely at Douglas on border 6 a.m. today. Estimated
                            that hundred and twenty Americans <pb facs="0793" n="677" xml:id="pg_677"/> came out. Cananea Consolidated Copper Company
                            closing its mine at Cananea tonight. Second special train being held
                            there to bring out all remaining Americans who will come.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>